caption: Regularly offers temporary exhibitions (free), for dates find out on their site.

A place certainly a little outdated but in an exceptional setting which allows you to come and see small temporary exhibitions, often free  The facade of the building is very beautiful  Presence of toilets in the building with free access  I recommend going there quickly
Great setting, but new website has become almost impossible to use. And above all, obviously, no more telephone switchboards exist and systematically refer to the Web...

Defense Historical Service. I confirm, you just need to change the order of the words. The reception was so deplorable that it was historic. In their defenses, they do not understand the concept of service.
I spoke with three people, and all three gave me conflicting information. In the end, the archivist was unaccommodating and extremely haughty.

Thank you to those who have the heavy task of preserving and therefore bringing to life with such care the memory of our heroes. The great human quality of the collaborators of the historical Defense service that I was able to meet today in the Louis Bravo to you, shadow resistance fighters.

Your site, which was so functional a few years ago, has become a gas factory! I'm still looking for the maquis directory in GR 19P, which previously took me a few seconds! And that's all I'm talking about...

Good morning I tried without success to search for the file of one of my ancestors, an officer under the empire. It is impossible for me to find the archive number and no one to answer the phone and no email address...It's a bit lamentable! M Chaze

An essential archive for working on the military history of France. The procedure for making an appointment is simple; Online inventories are accessible and allow you to prepare your work sessions. The welcome on site is pleasant. The reading room is large, pleasant and well lit. As for the staff, they are welcoming, competent and helpful.
Trying to contact a manager of this shd service or my loved one who works there and left a little while ago. We manage to get no one.

always so complicated to get a date, you have to arm yourself with monstrous patience to get access to the boxes. At this rate the request for ratings has time to enter the national archives before we can go on site
Very warm welcome. Total availability of competent and smiling staff (for a Saturday morning ;)). And an impeccable reading room for research work.

Faced with recurring problems concerning access to documents, the following steps should be taken: Referral to the Commission for Access to Administrative Documents for requests for access to public documents (theoretically freely communicable)... Then, despite the positive opinion of the Commission for Access to Administrative Documents, a new refusal leading to a contentious appeal to the Paris Administrative Court. The established procedure is simple: Request - Refusal = Cada followed by an Opinion (if favorable) new request - Refusal = Administrative Tribunal as part of a procedure in excess of power. Furthermore, for current malfunctions, a report to the Inspector General of the Armed Forces and the Controller General of the Armed Forces must be made. Elsewhere, an alert via the reporting platform of the Court of Auditors
Place steeped in history, interesting for carrying out research. A little lost at first, especially on how to consult the boxes.
Exhibition on 100 years of the Mobile Gendarmerie which closes on a Saturday afternoon at 3 p.m.!!! The SHD always equal to itself!!!
Always a pleasure to meet the team again. Thank you!
Unable to connect to the site to reserve the documents!!!!!
Efficient service; you just need to follow the -very clear- procedures indicated on the SHD website
Very competent team at the service of the public. Magnificent buildings!
Top, superb places between the 17th century pavilions and the Middle Ages dungeon.
A wealth of information for history and genealogy enthusiasts and professionals
